<title type="html"><![CDATA[loopyV update]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8228&amp;p=85280#p85280"><![CDATA[
At pixel #257 of the scanline, if background and sprites are enabled, these bits get copied:<br />v:.....x.....xxxxx=t:.....x.....xxxxx<br /><br />So it copies the 5 low bits, and the X nametable bit.  That's how it snaps back to the left side of the screen after it has drawn a scanline.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Wed Oct 19, 2011 12:20 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
